{
  "stem": "25651.13",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And with this rollwagen in the mud, the bodies would be loaded, and then they would slither through these, these fence-like leather-- the leather-type sides.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the men had to pick them up again and load them again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And now it was the same sort of thing, because somebody would die, he would be stripped naked, and he'd be thrown.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people would grab legs and hands, and two or three swings and then, up, and he'd fly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the body would fly like a pole vaulter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was telling you about my brothers being tremendous sportsmen, particularly Shragga.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He used to jump pole.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, they were Olympic-- all my brothers were Olympic-type sportsmen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Henry, for example, got third prize in a skiing competition in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Shragga could jump 16 feet or something, pole vaulting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the record was half a meter more or something like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I remember this curve, you know, that a pole vaulter-- and I thought of Shragga jumping like this, that these bodies were vaulting exactly like a pole vaulter, this backward roll.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we got to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the Buchenwald commandant refused to take us because Buchenwald was full.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So the journey continued somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I don't know how long it took, but it, it must have taken two weeks, probably more.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I don't remember how we were fed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Most of the time we were not fed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So we were terribly hungry, particularly thirsty.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "People would jump out of the train when it was in the sidings and risk their life to gather up the snow, you know, to, to drink, to have something on the lips.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
